    {
      "number": 5,
      "id": "I_kwDOKYa77857aTh_",
      "title": "Unaddressed Feedback from Reviews",
      "url": "https://github.com/scionassociation/scion-dp_I-D/issues/5",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "jiceatscion",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [
        "jiceatscion"
      ],
      "labels": [
        "Prio 1"
      ],
      "body": "General feedback Eliot: \r\n- [ ] Make sure the references are correct:\r\n       - Normative references: Needed for the specification; specification is based on it.\r\n       - Informative references: Provide background/additional information\r\n- [ ] Make sure MUST/MAY/SHOULD are used correctly (see also [RFC 8174](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8174)): \r\n       - MUST: Without this, the protocol will not work\r\n       - SHOULD: Should do this unless you have a very good reason not to\r\n       - MAY: Try to not use \"MAY\", Eliot is not a big fan of it\r\n- [ ] What text can be removed? Be concise. Make sure every word that is there must be there. \r\n\r\nFeedback Juan: \r\n- [ ] Explain\u00a0how to calculate the length in bytes of the `ExtLen` field in the SCION Hop-by-Hop/End-to-End Options header (extension\u00a0header of a SCION path header).\r\n- [ ] Explain why any transport or other upper-layer protocol that includes addresses from the SCION header in the checksum computation should use a pseudo header.\r\n- [ ] Simplify the \"Life of a packet\" figure, e.g., by removing all the IP addresses and listing them in a table instead, and/or having just numbers/letters as interface IDs.\r\n",
      "createdAt": "2024-01-08T13:45:04Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-01-08T13:45:05Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    }
  ],
